# The Little Bake Store - Implementation Plan

## Overview
AI-powered ecommerce web application for a Nigerian bakery brand built with Next.js 14, PostgreSQL, Paystack, and AI integrations.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router, SSR)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with CSS Variables (design tokens)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
- **Payments**: Paystack
- **Image Storage**: Amazon S3 (simulated with local storage initially)
- **AI**: Grok API / GPT-4 fallback
- **Deployment**: Vercel-optimized

## Phase 1: Foundation (Current Session)
1. Initialize Next.js project
2. Design system (CSS variables, fonts, global styles)
3. Navigation with mega menu dropdown
4. Homepage layout (hero, categories, trending, testimonials, footer)
5. Shop page with sidebar filters + product grid
6. Product detail page
7. Shopping cart (slide-out panel)
8. Checkout flow
9. BakeBot AI chat widget
10. Admin dashboard (basic)

## Phase 2: Backend & Database
- PostgreSQL schema with Prisma
- API routes for products, orders, users
- Authentication (admin login)
- Paystack integration

## Phase 3: AI Features
- BakeBot receptionist
- Product recommendation engine
- SEO automation
- Abandoned cart recovery
- Sales forecasting

## Design Tokens
- Primary: #4A2C2A (Chocolate Brown)
- Accent: #F7F3EF (Cream)
- Highlight: #D6A36D (Caramel)
- Background: #FFFFFF
- Text: #1A1A1A
- Heading Font: Playfair Display
- Body Font: Inter
